## Additional Terms for ZORA CORE

### Ethical Use Clause
This software is provided with the expectation that it will be used in accordance 
with the ethical principles outlined in ETHICS.md. Users are expected to:

1. Use the software for beneficial purposes that enhance human capabilities
2. Respect privacy and data protection principles
3. Avoid using the software for harmful, discriminatory, or malicious purposes
4. Comply with all applicable laws and regulations

### Attribution Requirements
When using ZORA CORE in derivative works or commercial applications:

1. Maintain attribution to the original ZORA CORE project
2. Include a link to the original repository: https://github.com/THEZORACORE/ZORA-CORE
3. Acknowledge the contributions of the ZORA CORE community

### AI Integration Compliance
Users integrating with AI services through ZORA CORE must:

1. Comply with the terms of service of all integrated AI providers
2. Respect rate limits and usage guidelines of AI services
3. Ensure proper API key management and security practices
4. Follow ethical AI development principles as outlined in our documentation

### Community Guidelines
This project is committed to fostering an inclusive and welcoming community:

1. All contributors and users are expected to follow our Code of Conduct
2. Discrimination, harassment, or harmful behavior is not tolerated
3. Community members should help maintain a positive and collaborative environment

### Disclaimer
ZORA CORE is provided as-is, and while we strive for reliability and security,
users are responsible for:

1. Proper configuration and security of their deployments
2. Compliance with applicable laws and regulations in their jurisdiction
3. Appropriate use of integrated AI services and APIs
4. Regular updates and maintenance of their ZORA CORE installations

For questions about licensing or usage, please contact: legal@zora-core.ai

